From: ETK GTK Edition <mercurious>
Subject: [PATCH v0.7.1] perf-stat SHM emit — attribute a slow frame (PPU/SPU/RSX)

The perf overlay already computes the per-subsystem frame split (PPU% / SPU% /
RSX%) at Detail=High, but it only lives on-screen. This mirrors those SAME
computed values to /dev/shm/rpcs3_perf_stat (+ a wall-clock rpcs3_perf_log
timeline), exactly like the aud= emitter (ffs-v4), so the ETK ledger can
attribute a pack-race bog to CPU-emulation vs GPU without the GUI.

Design note (why emit the overlay's own values, not a standalone sampler): the
cycle-delta accounting (thread_ctrl::get_cycles semantics) is subtle and lives in
the build-vol Utilities tree, not verified here. Emitting m_ppu_usage/m_spu_usage/
m_rsx_usage guarantees the SHM number == the number on screen — zero new math,
zero divergence risk. Cost: only fires when the overlay runs at Detail=High
(which the operator now toggles via the Pitstop Perf Overlay dials). A always-on
standalone sampler is the v0.7.2 follow-up, once get_cycles() delta-vs-cumulative
is confirmed against the build-vol source.

Gated at Detail=High because that is the only level where the full record is
fresh: high falls through to medium (sets ppu/spu/rsx) and itself sets frametime,
rsx_load and thread count. At <high those extra fields are stale.

Companion (separate, ETK repo): bin/session_postmortem.sh reads the SHM file into
a trailing ledger column `perf`; config/pitstop_fields.json exposes the overlay

--- a/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/Overlays/overlay_perf_metrics.cpp
+++ b/rpcs3/Emu/RSX/Overlays/overlay_perf_metrics.cpp	2026-07-10 12:52:24.355715449 +0000
@@ -11,6 +11,48 @@
 
 #include "util/cpu_stats.hpp"
 
+#include <cstdio>
+#include <ctime>
+
+namespace rsx
+{
+	namespace overlays
+	{
+		// ETK perf-stat SHM emit (v0.7.1, perfstat-v1). Mirror the overlay's OWN
+		// computed per-subsystem usage to /dev/shm so the ledger can attribute a
+		// slow frame (pack-bog: PPU/SPU/RSX split) with no GUI and no MangoHud.
+		// Same tmp+rename + bounded append-log pattern as the aud= emitter.
+		// fail-silent; Linux only (the rig). Values are exactly what the overlay
+		// draws, so ledger and screen can never disagree.
+		static void etk_perf_stats_dump(f32 fps, f32 ft_ms, f32 cpu,
+			f32 ppu, f32 spu, f32 rsx, u32 rsx_load, u32 threads)
+		{
+#ifdef __linux__
+			char line[256];
+			const int n = std::snprintf(line, sizeof(line),
+				"fps=%.1f ft_ms=%.2f cpu=%.1f ppu=%.1f spu=%.1f rsx=%.1f rsxload=%u thr=%u\n",
+				fps, ft_ms, cpu, ppu, spu, rsx, rsx_load, threads);
+			if (n <= 0) return;
+
+			if (std::FILE* f = std::fopen("/dev/shm/rpcs3_perf_stat.tmp", "w"))
+			{
+				std::fwrite(line, 1, static_cast<usz>(n), f);
+				std::fclose(f);
+				std::rename("/dev/shm/rpcs3_perf_stat.tmp", "/dev/shm/rpcs3_perf_stat");
+			}
+
+			if (std::FILE* tl = std::fopen("/dev/shm/rpcs3_perf_log", "a"))
+			{
+				std::fseek(tl, 0, SEEK_END);
+				if (std::ftell(tl) < 2 * 1024 * 1024)
+					std::fprintf(tl, "ep=%llu %s", static_cast<unsigned long long>(std::time(nullptr)), line);
+				std::fclose(tl);
+			}
+#endif
+		}
+	}
+}
+
 namespace rsx
 {
 	namespace overlays
@@ -577,6 +619,17 @@
 					}
 				}
 
+				// ETK: mirror the just-computed frame split to SHM for the ledger.
+				// Detail=High is the only level where the full record is fresh
+				// (high -> medium fallthrough sets ppu/spu/rsx; high itself sets
+				// frametime/rsx_load/threads). Operator arms High via the Pitstop
+				// Perf Overlay dials for a pack/audio attribution stint.
+				if (m_detail == detail_level::high)
+				{
+					etk_perf_stats_dump(m_fps, m_frametime, m_cpu_usage,
+						m_ppu_usage, m_spu_usage, m_rsx_usage, m_rsx_load, m_total_threads);
+				}
+
 				// 2. Format output string
 				std::string perf_text;
 
